## 🚀 New Features

### FEAT-001: Financial Screenshot Import (Robinhood/Fidelity/Schwab)
- **Status**: ✅ Completed
- **Priority**: 🔴 Critical
- **Files**: `src/SmartView.tsx`, `src/components/ImageScanModal.tsx`, `src/components/BankDashboard.tsx`, `src/components/PendingFinancialImportsModal.tsx`, `src/services/pendingFinancialImports.ts`, `api/scan-image.ts`
- **Issue**: Users want to quickly update investment account balances by scanning screenshots of their brokerage apps (Robinhood, Fidelity, Charles Schwab, etc.)
- **Solution**: Two-step secure workflow:
  1. **Scan Phase (Anywhere)**: User uploads screenshot → AI/OCR extracts financial data → Shows preview → Saves as PENDING with type FINANCIAL_SCREENSHOT
  2. **Approve Phase (Safe Only)**: Inside Safe → Financial tab shows "pending imports" badge → User reviews comparison (current vs scanned) → Accept/Edit/Dismiss
- **Workflow Details**:
  - Image scan detects financial data patterns (account names, balances, holdings)
  - Shows read-only preview outside Safe
  - Displays message: "To update Bank Records, go to Safe → Financial"
  - Inside Safe: Shows side-by-side diff, allows Accept/Edit/Dismiss per item
  - Can create new accounts OR update existing balances
- **Security Requirements**:
  - NO auto-updates - every change requires explicit user approval
  - Must be inside unlocked Safe to approve changes
  - Audit trail: log all imports with timestamp, source, old/new values
- **Completed Date**: 2026-03-11
- **Notes**: 
  - Supports Robinhood, Fidelity, Schwab, Vanguard, E*Trade, Zerodha, Groww, Coinbase
  - Shows confidence score and source detection
  - Holdings preview with expandable details
  - Match existing accounts or create new ones

### FEAT-002: Image Scan Context Hints (Keywords + Financial Flag)
- **Status**: ✅ Completed
- **Priority**: 🟡 Medium
- **Files**: `src/SmartView.tsx`, `src/components/ImageScanModal.tsx`, `api/scan-image.ts`, `src/services/imageScanning/openaiVisionService.ts`, `src/services/imageScanning/tesseractService.ts`, `src/services/imageScanning/imageParser.ts`
- **Issue**: AI cannot reliably detect source app (e.g., Robinhood screenshot shows "Investing $6,153.31" but no app name). User has no way to provide context hints to improve scan accuracy.
- **Solution**: Added two optional fields in ImageScanModal (shown after image selected):
  1. **Keywords/Context** (free text): User provides hints like "robinhood investing", "birthday invitation", "costco receipt"
  2. **Financial Information** (checkbox): User indicates this is for Bank Dashboard / Safe section
- **Logic**:
  - Keywords passed to GPT-4 Vision prompt with higher weight for context
  - Financial checkbox OR AI-detected financial data → routes to Safe section pending imports
  - Both fields optional - enhances accuracy when provided
- **Applies To**:
  - GPT-based image scan (keywords added to prompt)
  - Free image scan path (imageParser detects financial patterns)
- **Completed Date**: 2026-03-12
- **Notes**: 
  - UI shows context fields after image preview, before scan button
  - ScanContextHints interface exported from ImageScanModal
  - detectFinancialData() added to imageParser for quick scan financial detection

